cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and machine translation. The use of syntactic information in the proposed model also suggests a possible fit with the sub-category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The attention mechanism used in the model may also make it relevant to the sub-category cs.LG (Learning). Additionally, the use of neural networks in the model may suggest a possible fit with the sub-categories cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
